content.description: Climb the steep slab/face on good rock to the anchors.
content.location: Near the right end of the Missoureality wall, this is the short bolted line between Missoureality and Osceolabotomy.

content.description: 20 yds past missourireality wall, 6 bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Typical slab start,  follow obvious line to the bulge then climb up and slightly right.
Climb the steep slab/face past bolts to the anchors.  Good rock.
content.location: Near the left end of the Missoureality area, this is just right of Slab 94.

content.description: Steep slab/face climbing arching to the right.  Be careful going to the anchors, it's a tiny runout.  Pretty good rock.
content.location: 3rd route from the left on the Missoureality area, just right of Chalk a Khan.  This is the right-arching line of bolts on the slab.

content.description: Climb the large dihedral, arching left, until you come to the tree about 2/3 up.  Here, traverse left to more holds.  Take these up to the offwidth dihedral, pulling up on the right side.  Mostly good rock.
content.protection: Bolts, gear to 4" or so, 2-bolt anchor.  Rap, lower, or maybe walk off.
content.location: Near the right end of the Missoureality area, this line follows the large dihedral system that arches to the left.

content.description: Climb the steep stab to the thin crack.  Follow it to the base of the roof.  Then, surmount the roof via the steep handcrack and holds.  Some of the rock at the roof may be a tiny bit chossy, but there is good rock overall.
content.protection: Gear to 3", a bolt or two, 2-bolt anchor.  Rap, lower, or walk off.
content.location: Near the right end of the Missoureality area, this line starts below the roof crack way above and the thin crack on the face.

content.description: Low-angled slab climbing on decent rock.
content.location: The farthest route left in the Missoureality area.  Start on the slab beneath 2 bolts.

content.description: More steep slab/face climbing on pretty good rock.
content.location: Near the middle of the Missoureality area, this is the next route right of Slab 94.

content.description: Low angled slab climbing on decent rock.
content.location: 2nd route from the left in the Missoureality area.  Begins on low-angled slab.

content.description: Climb the face up to the base of the roof area on the right.  Pull around the left side of it on chossy rock and to the anchors below the lip.  Pretty good rock until the last 15 feet.
content.location: Near the middle of the Missoureality area, this begins left of the roof system up high.

content.description: Mostly good quality rock.  Mostly slab, but a little vertical stuff.
